<p>I think the trick to a BIG, BIG flavor in any almond cakes is pure almond extract (not the imitation one, yuck!)? That&#39;s what I think, at least. Even when I&#39;m supposed to be something maply, with GLUGS and GLUGS of PURE maple syrup poured in (which is very expensive in Malaysia, apropos), the end product doesn&#39;t taste intensely maply at all. I have to use Mapleine to make up for that, just like what my American &#8220;mom&#8221; does with hers &#8211; her famous pumpkin bars with maply frosting. I wouldn&#39;t consider that cheating. Haha!</p>
<p>P.S. I&#39;ve been enjoying reading your book. =)</p>
