    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have a cake recipe that calls for a 9-inch round cake pan, and that cake, too, always falls in the center.  One time I tried using a 9&#215;9 square pan and voila!  It worked!  Not sure why it works, as the area of a 9&#215;9 (81&#8243;) is actually greater than the area of a 9-inch round (63.6) but it does.  So it might work for the almond cake.</p>
